u003cpath d=\"M18 3.5v8l-1.5 1.5h-15l-1.5-1.5v-8l1.5-1.5h3.5l2-2h4l2 2h3.5l1.5 1.5zm-9 7.5c1.9 0 3.5-1.6 3.5-3.5s-1.6-3.5-3.5-3.5-3.5 1.6-3.5 3.5 1.6 3.5 3.5 3.5z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe scenery is ‘otherworldly’ around Porto village.\u003c/span\u003e Photograph: Jan Wlodarczyk/Alamy\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003ePeaceful little Porto nestles at the craggy pink toes of the Calanques de Piana on the north-west shoulder of Corsica. Aside from the delightful pebble beach offering views of lingering sunsets with occasional dolphin sightings, there is the pretty village with restaurants that creeps up behind the beach (try \u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/l_ora_porto/\" data-link-name=\"in body link\"\u003eL’Ora\u003c/a\u003e on the quayside for a sundowner and a tasty crepe or two with the all-important west-facing view), bounteous walks in the otherworldy scenery, azure natural river pools for swimming, meandering mountain roads and exhilarating boat tours. Porto is a somewhat thrilling two-hour drive from Calvi and capital city Ajaccio.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAnna Kennett\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"df384459-fd49-40e9-91f3-412b08ebfa54\" data-spacefinder-role=\"inline\" data-spacefinder-type=\"model.dotcomrendering.pageElements.ProfileAtomBlockElement\"\u003e\u003cgu-island name=\"ProfileAtomWrapper\" priority=\"feature\" deferuntil=\"visible\" props=\"{\u0026#34;id\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;9a19fac5-8dff-4125-9ba7-ba08f2c09fa7\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;Readers\u0026#39; tips: send a tip for a chance to win a £200 voucher for a Coolstays break\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;html\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;\u0026lt;strong\u0026gt; Guardian Travel readers\u0026#39; tips\u0026lt;/strong\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;Every week we ask our readers for recommendations from their travels. A selection of tips will be featured onli